---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Privacy Policy | SexualHarassmentCalc';
const description = 'Privacy policy for SexualHarassmentCalc: what we collect, third-party advertising, the case-review form, and your rights.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><em>Updated July 2026.</em></p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how SexualHarassmentCalc (&ldquo;the Site,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us&rdquo;) collects,
    uses, and shares information about visitors. The Site is operated by The Click Lab Agency LLC and is informational only.
  </p>

  <h2>Information we collect</h2>
  <p>
    The Site does not require accounts, and simply browsing the calculator, guides, and other content does not require you to
    provide personal information. We collect the following:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Server logs.</strong> Standard request logs including IP address, user-agent string, referring URL, and timestamp. Used for security, abuse prevention, and aggregate traffic analysis.</li>
    <li><strong>Calculator inputs.</strong> Values you enter into the calculator itself are processed in your browser only and are not transmitted to or stored on our servers.</li>
    <li><strong>Case-review form.</strong> If you choose to submit the &ldquo;Sexual Harassment&rdquo; case-review form on the homepage, we collect your name, phone number, email address, the case details you provide, and a timestamp of your consent. This is separate from using the calculator and is entirely optional &mdash; see the next section for what happens to this information.</li>
    <li><strong>Email correspondence.</strong> If you email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>, we retain the message and your email address to respond. We do not share or republish reader correspondence.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>The case-review form and attorney sharing</h2>
  <p>
    If you submit the case-review form, your name, phone number, email address, and case details are shared with one or more
    attorneys or their agents licensed to practice in your jurisdiction, so they can evaluate your situation and contact you
    about it. The Click Lab Agency LLC, which operates SexualHarassmentCalc, is not a law firm, does not provide legal advice,
    and does not vet, endorse, or guarantee the attorneys in this network. Submitting the form does not create an
    attorney-client relationship with The Click Lab Agency LLC or with any attorney until and unless that attorney separately
    agrees to represent you. The Click Lab Agency LLC may be compensated for these referrals.
  </p>
  <p>
    By submitting the form, you separately consent to be contacted by phone, text, and email &mdash; including by automated
    dialing technology &mdash; by The Click Lab Agency LLC and the attorneys or agents your information is shared with. That
    consent is not required to use any other part of this site, and you can decline it by not submitting the form.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-party advertising</h2>
  <p>
    The Site displays advertising through <strong>Google AdSense</strong> (publisher ID pub-6434377544325972) and uses Google
    Analytics (measurement ID G-RSPFE68DY3). Google and its advertising partners may use cookies, web beacons, and similar
    technologies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this site and other sites. Google&rsquo;s use of advertising
    cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit to our site and other sites on the internet. You can
    opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://adssettings.google.com">Google Ads Settings</a> or
    <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices">www.aboutads.info/choices</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Cookies</h2>
  <p>
    Beyond analytics and advertising scripts described above, the Site does not set additional first-party tracking cookies.
    You can disable cookies entirely in your browser settings; some site features may not work, but the calculator and all
    content will remain available.
  </p>

  <h2>Children</h2>
  <p>
    The Site is not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you
    believe a child has provided personal information through the Site, contact us and we will delete it.
  </p>

  <h2>Opting out</h2>
  <p>
    The simplest opt-out is not to submit the case-review form &mdash; every other part of the Site (the calculator, guides,
    and articles) is fully usable without providing any personal information. If you already submitted the form and want your
    information removed or want to withdraw consent to be contacted, email
    <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the subject line <code>[OPT-OUT]</code>, or visit
    <a href="https://theclicklab.agency/optout">theclicklab.agency/optout</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Your rights (CCPA/CPRA and GDPR)</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have rights to request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal
    information we hold about you, and to opt out of certain processing.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>California residents:</strong> sharing your information with attorneys for compensation, as described above, may
    be considered a &ldquo;sale&rdquo; or &ldquo;share&rdquo; of personal information under the CCPA/CPRA. You have the right
    to opt out of this at any time using the channels in the &ldquo;Opting out&rdquo; section above. Anonymous browsing of the
    calculator and guides alone is never sold or shared, because it doesn&rsquo;t involve any personal information.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>EU/UK residents:</strong> the legal basis for processing the information you submit through the case-review form
    is your consent, which you may withdraw at any time using the same channels. The legal basis for server logs and analytics
    is our legitimate interest in operating and securing the Site.
  </p>
  <p>
    To exercise any of these rights, email <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a> with the page
    URL and the nature of your request. We respond within 30 days.
  </p>

  <h2>Data retention</h2>
  <p>
    Server logs are retained for up to 90 days. Case-review form submissions are retained for as long as needed to fulfill the
    referral and for a reasonable period afterward for record-keeping, unless you request deletion sooner. Email
    correspondence is retained as long as needed to respond and for a reasonable period afterward for audit and abuse
    prevention.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    The Site is served over HTTPS. No internet transmission is fully secure; do not include information in email or the
    case-review form that you would not be comfortable putting in a non-confidential medium.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy as the Site evolves or as law requires. Material changes will be reflected in the
    &ldquo;Updated&rdquo; date at the top of this page. Continued use of the Site after a change constitutes acceptance.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this policy: <a href="mailto:hey@theclicklab.agency">hey@theclicklab.agency</a>.
  </p>
</BaseLayout>
